From 7b5d45e64e2d98e6cbc09cac95140a411f48de53 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Hubert <hubert@localhost>
Date: Wed, 8 Jul 2026 11:45:16 +0200
Subject: [PATCH] yad: remove --image-on-top and --decorated/--undecorated (Yad
 >=15.0 compat)
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Yad 15.0 no longer silently ignores unknown options and instead exits
with code 255 on parse errors. Two long-removed Yad options were still
being passed by STL in every dialog:

- --image-on-top: removed from all Yad calls (32 occurrences)
- --decorated / --undecorated (via $WINDECO): removed from all Yad
  calls and the prepareGUI function (51 occurrences)

The USEWINDECO config variable is preserved for backward compatibility
but is now a no-op. Users who previously set USEWINDECO=0 to disable
window decorations on X11 will need to configure this at the window
manager level instead.

Tested on Yad 14.2 and 15.0 — all dialogs work. bash -n passes clean.
---
